<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>long clothes • long robes</xh5><p> <i>long clothes—</i>long dress for a baby’s body: But before he was out of <u>long clothes</u>, the cloven foot began to show; he developed a taste for low pleasures.</p><p><i>long robes—</i>long, loose garment worn as a sign of rank or office by judges, priests, etc.: In most nations judges wear <u>long robes</u>, usually black or red, and sit on an elevated platform during trials.</p> </entry>
